The paper deals with the computational complexity of computing and deciding the positivity of plethysm coefficients, which are related to the coordinate rings of spaces of polynomials. This falls under the area of algebraic complexity theory, which is typically classified under cs.CC. The paper also uses techniques from discrete tomography, which could place it under cs.DS or cs.CG. Additionally, the paper involves combinatorial descriptions of plethysm coefficients, which could fall under cs.SC.
